grep [-i] [-n] [-c] <pattern> <file>

  Search for a pattern in a file and print matching lines.
  Pattern matching is substring-based (no regular expressions).

  Options:
    -i    case-insensitive matching
    -n    prefix each matching line with its line number
    -c    print only a count of matching lines

  Examples:
    grep help /sys/help/index
    grep -i HELP /sys/help/index
    grep -n cat /sys/help/index
    grep -c the /sys/help/ls
